     <div type="encomium">
   <head>To the Translator my Friend.</head>
   <l>ME thinkes I heare our age complaine,</l>
   <l>That ev'ry sicke and crazy braine</l>
   <l>Which ha's a tympany within't,</l>
   <l>Do's cure it selfe by being in print;</l>
   <l>And that she feares, bands being so small,</l>
   <l>The price of paper will marre all:</l>
   <l>I cannot blame her, since we fill</l>
   <l>Our Presses (which ne're yet stood still)</l>
   <l>With such stuffe, as t'were a sin</l>
   <l>To wrap Tobacco, or Macrell in.</l>
   <l>But for thy booke (judicious Friend)</l>
   <l>Upon it I'le this censure spend;</l>
   <l>That to perpetuate our tongue,</l>
   <l>This issue from thy phancy sprung:</l>
   <l>
      <pb facs="12"/>For should an <hi>English</hi> word e're dye,</l>
   <l>Hence might we fetch a new supply.</l>
   <l>
      <hi>Greece</hi> shall not us <hi>Barbarians</hi> call,</l>
   <l>Thy <hi>Atticke</hi> stile ha's free'd us all.</l>
   <closer>
      <signed>T. C.</signed>
   </closer>
</div>
